modules.description: This module implements an Adaptive Radix Tree (ART) for efficient in-memory indexing with support for fast key-based lookups, insertions, deletions, and ordered traversal. It works with string keys and arbitrary value types, maintaining entries in sorted order to enable range scans, prefix searches, and min/max queries. Concrete use cases include high-performance in-memory databases, routing tables, and auto-complete systems where dynamic key management and ordered iteration are required.
